    thinking: "**Defining the Architecture**\n\nI\'ve determined the current `package.json` configurations are basic, running `vite` for development and building. The Gemini API necessitates a full-stack approach, specifically Express with Vite. I am settling on a default full-stack architecture.\n\n\n**Updating the Scripts**\n\nI\'m now focusing on implementing the server-side API routes and ensuring all API keys, especially the Gemini key, are securely hidden. My immediate task is editing the `package.json` scripts to align with the full-stack app requirements. I will update the `\"dev\"`, `\"build\"`, and `\"start\"` scripts according to the specified instructions.\n\n\n**Considering Dependencies**\n\nI\'m now thinking about the necessary dependencies. For charting, I\'m leaning toward `recharts` since that\'s suggested, though I briefly considered custom SVG charts. It appears I need CSV parsing, and I\'m deciding between writing a basic JS parser or using `papaparse` \342\200\223 a simple parser might be best to keep the project light. I\'ll evaluate both options.\n\n\n**Designing the Interface**\n\nI am now leaning toward custom SVG charts using Tailwind, which has become a clear choice given React 19 compatibility. This approach will offer extensive customization and eliminate potential compilation issues. I\'m prioritizing a clean, medical aesthetic for the dashboard, considering high-contrast color schemes, and have settled on \"CardiaSense AI\" for the app\'s name. I am verifying any other dependencies I might require.\n\n\n"
