  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining Server Architecture**\n\nI\'ve decided to tackle the Express backend next, beginning with `server.ts`. I\'m focusing on key server functions: initializing the Gemini API using the `GEMINI_API_KEY` environment variable and properly serving static files from the `dist` directory in production, or mounting the Vite dev server in development.\n\n\n**Designing API Endpoints**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the `/api/analyze-patient` POST endpoint. It\'ll receive patient data and prediction results, then forward a request to Gemini 3.5. My goal is to structure Gemini\'s output as JSON for easy rendering into clinical cards. I\'m aiming for structured risk analysis and clear interpretations. I\'ll need to define a `responseSchema` for JSON output.\n\n\n**Refining JSON Schema**\n\nI\'ve got the JSON schema defined for the Gemini output now. It\'s clean, compliant with the `@google/genai` type definitions, and it\'ll streamline the prediction rendering into clinical cards. I\'m building out `server.ts` with strict `@google/genai` integration and explicit API routes to handle the requests properly. Environment variables are loaded, and ports are configured.\n\n\n**Implementing API Routes**\n\nI\'ve set up the core Express app and configured it to use JSON middleware. I\'ve also implemented the `/api/analyze` POST route to handle requests for clinical analysis. It checks for the presence of patient and prediction data in the request body, and it handles the case where the Gemini API client isn\'t initialized, including instructions for the user. I\'m now focusing on constructing the prompt for Gemini.\n\n\n**Crafting Gemini Prompt**\n\nI\'m now writing the prompt for the Gemini model. It\'ll receive detailed patient information and predictive interpretations. The prompt will request structured risk analysis and clear interpretations. I\'m focusing on providing context for the AI, so it can act as a professional cardiologist AI. I\'m aiming for concise, actionable outputs.\n\n\n**Formulating Clinical Guidance**\n\nI\'m now integrating the prompt with specific instructions for the Gemini model. I\'ve instructed it to deliver in-depth explanations of risk categories based on physiological and clinical metrics. It should offer personalized lifestyle changes, medical examination recommendations, and potential clinical watch-outs in a concise yet authoritative manner. I\'m aiming for actionable and medically sound advice.\n\n\n**Validating Gemini Response**\n\nI\'m now focused on validating the Gemini API\'s output. I\'m checking for text content in the `response` to prevent empty responses. I\'ll need to parse the response to JSON and make sure it conforms to the pre-defined `responseSchema`. I\'m verifying the presence of \"clinicalInterpretation\" and \"recommendations\" and their formats, so I can trust the structured output.\n\n\n**Finalizing Response Handling**\n\nI\'m now implementing robust error handling and response management for the API endpoint. I\'ve integrated `try...catch` blocks to gracefully handle potential errors during Gemini API calls. I\'m verifying the structure and validity of Gemini\'s JSON response to ensure accurate data parsing and prevent unexpected issues in clinical card rendering. I\'ve added a Vite integration to properly serve static files.\n\n\n**Implementing Health Check**\n\nI\'ve just added a health check endpoint, `/api/health`, so I can verify the server is running and the API key is configured. I\'ve also implemented lazy initialization of the GoogleGenAI client, and now I\'m working on the `/api/analyze` route to make sure it handles the data.\n\n\n\n**Constructing Prompt Details**\n\nI\'m now integrating detailed patient data into the Gemini prompt, including age, sex, and clinical metrics such as chest pain type and blood pressure, along with prediction results. I\'m formatting it so it\'s easy for the AI to parse. The prompt now includes specific instructions for Gemini to provide in-depth physiological explanations and suggest personalized lifestyle and medical recommendations.\n\n\n**Analyzing Indicator Synergy**\n\nI\'m now focusing on how specific indicators interact, like the relationship between ST slope trends and ischemia or how blood pressure and age impact this. I\'m aiming for authoritative, clear explanations, and I\'ll include a professional medical disclaimer. I am formulating recommendations, and I want them to be specific and actionable. I\'m focusing on clinical terms, such as \"echocardiogram\", and I need to target 4-5 items.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create the `/server.ts` file, establishing the full-stack server with Vite middleware integration and our secure `/api/analyze` Gemini endpoint. This keeps our clinical AI evaluation logic 100% server-side and robust."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 17
      nanos: 394646323
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
