    modified_response: "I have successfully built and configured **CardioSphere AI**\342\200\224a highly polished, clinical-grade Heart Failure Prediction & Predictive Analytics platform aligned with the real-world dataset on Kaggle.\n\nThe system compiles, lints, and executes flawlessly on our Node.js full-stack container workspace.\n\n### \360\237\214\237 Key Functional Features Completed\n\n1. **Rule-Based Engine (fedesoriano/heart-failure-prediction Dataset Standard)**\n   - Calculates precise risk probabilities based on clinical variables such as **ST Segment Slope** (Up/Flat/Down), **Exercise-Induced Angina**, **Asymptomatic indicators (ASY)**, **Oldpeak (ST depression)**, and hemodynamic factors.\n   - Provides automated classification of Low, Moderate, High, or Critical cardiac risks accompanied by physiological descriptions.\n\n2. **Advanced Patient Checklist Diagnostic Form**\n   - Enables doctors or users to enter metrics manually.\n   - Explains parameters (Typical vs. Atypical Angina, Chronotropic health expected thresholds, etc.).\n   - Generates instant risk score updates locally.\n\n3. **Gemini Pro Doctor AI Consultant Proxy**\n   - Calls **Gemini 3.5 Flash** on the secure Express backend to translate numbers into readable cardiology reports detailing dangerous factor synergies and custom screening pathways (e.g. *echocardiograms*, *cardiac MRIs*, and *angiograms*).\n\n4. **Bulk CSV Spreadsheet Scanner**\n   - High-throughput drag-and-drop table compiler.\n   - Automatically maps column variations (e.g. `ST_Slope`, `Umur`, `NyeriDada`, `Exang`) to the standard database schema.\n   - Includes a **Download sample CSV** trigger so you can test it instantly!\n\n5. **Recharts Clinical Graphics & Histograms**\n   - **Risk Level Distribution (Donut Chart)**: Percentage of patients matching each risk stage.\n   - **Anginal Chest Pain Distribution**: Frequency of symptoms (highlighting danger zones like ASY chest pain).\n   - **ST Slope Cohorts**: Side-by-side angiographic indicators.\n   - **Hemodynamic Stress Tolerance (Area Curve)**: Age versus peak heart rate comparison.\n\n6. **Full Database Actions & Export (Fulfilling Your Requirement)**\n   - Allows search, pagination, and multi-tier filters of patient records.\n   - Features a **\"Export Database (CSV)\"** button so you can instantly download your diagnostic list (with the calculated probabilities) to take it back to your local computer or machine learning model!\n"
