    thinking: "**Initiating Indonesian Translation**\n\nOkay, I\'m starting to translate the code, specifically `/src/components/AnalyticsCharts.tsx` into Indonesian. I\'ve begun with lines 17-21, focusing on the labels for risk levels. I\'m considering the best Indonesian words for \"Low Risk,\" \"Moderate Risk,\" etc., and how they\'ll fit within the chart\'s design. I\'ll need to consider cultural nuances to ensure the terms are appropriate.\n\n\n**Refining Indonesian Terms**\n\nI\'ve refined the Indonesian translation of the risk level labels. \"Risiko Rendah,\" \"Risiko Sedang,\" \"Risiko Tinggi,\" and \"Risiko Kritis\" are confirmed, and I\'ve updated the code accordingly. Now, I\'m working on lines 27-30, focusing on the translation of chest pain types like \"TA (Typical Angina),\" \"ATA (Atypical Angina),\" etc. I am evaluating direct translations and potential adaptations for clarity and cultural appropriateness in the Indonesian context.\n\n\n**Adapting Code for Pain**\n\nI\'ve translated the chest pain type labels. \"TA (Typical Angina)\" is now \"TA (Angina Tipikal),\" \"ATA (Atypical Angina)\" is \"ATA (Angina Atipikal),\" \"NAP (Non-Anginal Pain)\" is \"NAP (Nyeri Non-Anginal),\" and \"ASY\" is \"Asimtomatik\". Next, I\'ve moved on to lines 37-39, translating the ST slope descriptions. \"Upsloping\" is now \"Menanjak,\" \"Flat\" is \"Datar,\" and \"Downsloping\" is \"Menurun,\" and I believe these translations are quite accurate.\n\n\n**Translating Dashboard Metrics**\n\nI\'m now translating the dashboard metrics. Specifically, I\342\200\231ve handled the cases where cardiology metadata is unavailable and have translated related instructions. I\'ve tackled the \"Total Patient Pool\" section and associated gender distribution labels, and further worked on translating the age range details. Also, I\'ve updated the \"Identified High-Risk Cases\" and \"Critical Stage Cohort\" sections, with probability and cohort terms, respectively.\n\n\n**Expanding Indonesian Translation**\n\nI\'ve translated more text now. The priority clinical monitoring action status is updated. I\'ve also completed the sections for overall cardiac risk partitioning, anginal chest pain distribution, and electrocardiographic ST slope cohorts. Now, I\'m working on hemodynamic stress tolerance curve elements. I feel I am making good progress translating each section carefully. I\'m focusing on accuracy and clarity within the Indonesian context.\n\n\n**Updating Indonesian Dashboard**\n\nI\'ve translated more dashboard elements, including age comparison with maximum achieved heart rate, and \"Age\" and \"Max HR\" to \"Usia\" and \"Detak Jantung Maksimal.\" I\'ve also updated \"Peak Heart Rate:\" and \"Calculated risk probability:\" labels. Further, I\'ve worked on the \"General Cardiologic Profile Summary\" and the associated sentence.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will edit `/src/components/AnalyticsCharts.tsx` to completely translate the labels, card descriptions, chart legends, axes titles, tooltips, and clinician advisory notes into Indonesian."
